Shell Scripting is highly used for
 - Automating repititive tasks
 - back up and maintenance of databases
 - Running Cron jobs- Cron jobs are used to automating tasks that run on the background periodically, e.g. in web applications like LiveAgent.
TYpes of shells
- Bourne Shell (sh)
- Korn shell (ksh)
- Bourne Again Shell (bash)
- POSIX shell (sh)
- C shell (csh)
- TENEX/TOPS C Shell (tcsh)

EXECUTING SHELL SCRIPT
To execute a script file we need to assign an executable permission by using one of the following commands
chmod +x script-name.bash
chmod 755 script-name.bash

TO RUN A SHELL SCRIPT
To run a shell script u can follow any one of the following ways
./script-name.bash 
bash script-name.bash


ASSIGNING VARIABLES:
read -  read command allows you to prompt for input and store it in a variable.
